Fasting is overrated. 
For those who did not understand that
Overrated meaning: valued too highly or have a higher opinion of (someone or something) than is deserved.

There is nothing called as "gut health." Microbiome scientists have never identified or defined what a "healthy microbiome in the gut is," but have only figured out some beneficial gut bacteria.

Every holistic coach, every alternative medicine practitioner, every half-baked gastroenterologist (*cough* Pal *cough* *cough*), every overconfident nutritionist and science-defying dietitian-influencer on the internet has abused the word "gut health" so much that it has started featuring on Ayurvedic, Homeopathic and Naturopathic products which science-illiterate people lap up wholesale.

Fast is you feel like it. If you can tolerate it. If you are pious and your religion warrants it.

quotedTweet.rawContent:
Here’s an old Ottoman joke that I translated some time ago.
This is a Nasreddin Khoja joke:

One day a man walks up to the Khoja and asks him: “Who are you?”

(Some people back then but more so now associate their occupation or position with who they are)

Khoja responds quickly:
“هيچ Hiç, Nothing, I’m a nobody”

Noticing that the man was unimpressed by his response, the Khoja then asks him, “And, who are you?”

The man says proudly that he is an administrator for the Governor.

The Khoja then asks him,
“Who will you be after that?”

The man says, “Perhaps, I will be a Governor myself”

Khoja asks him, “Then who?”

The man says, “Perhaps a Vizier”

Khoja pushes him, “Then who?”

The man says, “Perhaps a Grand-vizier”

Khoja persists, “and then who will you be after that?”

The man knowing very well that he can never be a Sultan says disquietingly: “هيچ Hiç, Nothing”.

Khoja responds gleefully:

“Well my good man, why are you then boasting about who you are, when I’m already at the position that you seek to be many years from now!”
